# Citation integrity & no plagiarism

- Every citation must resolve to a verifiable real work (DOI, arXiv id, ACL
  Anthology id, or stable URL checked at cite time). No fabricated references.
- **Never cite arXiv:2605.12548** ("Cubical Type Theoretic Navya-Nyāya") — it is
  fabricated (see ADR 0008).
- No plagiarism: paraphrase and attribute; quote sparingly with quotation marks
  and a citation. Do not copy prose from sources.
- The literature review must be honest about limitations and prior art, including
  work that complicates PSALM's claims.
- Before any dissemination-phase closure, verify the entire bibliography resolves.
